12. Definitions

    "Compatible License" means a license listed in Appendix A. The
    non-inclusion of a license in Appendix A does not necessarily mean
    that distribution of Covered Code incorporating material governed by
    that license violates section 2 of this License.
    
    "Copyleft-Next Project" means the project that maintains the source
    code repository at <https://github.com/richardfontana/copyleft-next/>
    as of the release date of this License.

    "Covered Code" means My Code or an Enhancement.

    "Enhancement" means a derivative work, collective work or compilation,
    or a work that contains all or part of My Code. But the following are
    not Enhancements:
    (i) Mere Aggregation;
    (ii) a mere reproduction of My Code;
    (iii) if My Code fails to explicitly state an expectation otherwise, a
    work that merely makes reference to My Code; or
    (iv) if My Code provides a Public Interface, other software (alone or
    in combination with My Code) that merely interacts with My Code by way
    of the Public Interface.

    "I"/"Me"/"My" refers to the individual or legal entity that places My
    Work under this License.

    "Mere Aggregation" means an aggregation of Covered Code with a
    Separate Work.

    "My Code" means the particular work of authorship I license to You
    under this License.

    "Public Interface" means FIXME.

    "Separate Work" means a work that is separate from and independent of
    particular Covered Code and is not by its nature an extension or
    enhancement of the Covered Code, and/or is a runtime library, standard
    library, or similar component that is used to generate an Object Code
    form of Covered Code..

    "Source Code" means the preferred form of a work for making
    modifications to it.

    "You"/"Your" refers to the individual or legal
    entity exercising rights in My Code under this License.

